U.K. Conservatives’ Support Rises After Budget, ICM Poll Shows

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   P u r v i s
-- 
2011-03-26T13:11:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-26/u-k-conservatives-support-rises-after-budget-icm-poll-shows.html
U.K. voters’ backing for the
governing Conservative party increased after Chancellor of the
Exchequer  George Osborne  delivered his second budget, an ICM
poll for the  Guardian newspaper , published today, shows.  Support for the Conservatives rose 2 percentage points to
37 percent and backing for the opposition  Labour Party  fell 2
points to 36 percent, according to the poll. The Liberal
Democrats, currently governing in a coalition with the
Conservatives, were at 16 percent, down 2 percentage points from
the previous poll. Other parties had 11 percent support, a gain
of 2 percentage points.  ICM Research interviewed a random sample of 1,014 people on
March 23 and March 24 for the poll, the Guardian said. The
chancellor delivered his budget to Parliament on March 23.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Purvis in London at 
 bpurvis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net  